    <title>Intel is releasing another microcode update to protect crashing Raptor Lake CPUs</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="A 14th Gen Intel Core i9 processor on a blue Intel box" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4pXk2JNjA4XHz11t0LngPDO-XI4=/0x0:2543x1695/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73611224/intel14900k.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Photo by Tom Warren / The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="ec9lto"&gt;Get ready for another wave of urgent motherboard updates for your desktop PC. Intel has just announced a new microcode update for its 13th and 14th Gen Raptor Lake processors — &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/24216305/intel-13th-14th-gen-raptor-lake-cpu-crash-news-updates-patches-fixes-motherboards"&gt;the ones that could possibly get permanently damaged and begin to crash your PC&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="iNHP0O"&gt;While there’s still &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206529/intel-13th-14th-gen-crashing-instability-cpu-voltage-q-a"&gt;no fix for chips that are already crashing&lt;/a&gt;, the company is now releasing microcode update 0x12B to motherboard manufacturers to help prevent one of the root causes of damage. In this case, it prevents the Intel CPU from asking for too much power when it’s just sitting idle or performing light tasks. (Too much voltage can prematurely age a chip.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="c-float-left c-float-hang"&gt;&lt;aside id="XZ2lSA"&gt;&lt;div data-anthem-component="readmore" data-anthem-component-data='{"stories":[{"title":"Will PC makers replace your crashing Intel chip? We asked 15 of them","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215440/intel-13th-14th-gen-crash-raptor-lake-integrator-warranty-lenovo-dell-hp-acer-asus"},{"title":"There is no fix for Intel’s crashing 13th and 14th Gen CPUs — any damage is permanent ","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206529/intel-13th-14th-gen-crashing-instability-cpu-voltage-q-a"},{"title":"Intel’s crashing 13th and 14th Gen CPUs get two additional years of warranty coverage","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/1/24211616/intel-crashing-13th-14th-gen-cpus-warranty-two-more-years"}]}'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/aside&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="qydLBI"&gt;Intel says it may take several weeks for motherboard manufacturers to validate and roll out BIOS updates across their...&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;
    &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/25/24254611/intel-13th-14th-gen-crashes-september-2024-microcode-0x12b"&gt;Continue reading&amp;hellip;&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/p&gt;

</content>
